    #Abstract
      #abs
        #absw 
          h1 Abstract
        #fullabs
          p Coffee cultivation in Bangladesh getting popular among farmers day by day. Since 1990 at Chattogram to now Bangladesh is producing  avobe 55.75 tonnes of coffee per year. Curretly two types of coffee are produced in Bangladesh. One of them is robusta which are made from the beans of Coffea Canefora. The yield production quality of coffee is affecting various kind of diseases. Most of them are leaf diseases like Redmite and Rust. Farmers waste a lot of time and money and they identify infections with their bare hands and naked eyes, which leads to unhealthy farming. In this case the improvements of agricultural technical assistance substantially aids in the automatic identification of harmful microorganisms in coffee plant leaves. So we have developed a website for diseases detection by image of the leaf's using Keras Models (ResNet50V2, 93%Accuracy, 50epochs). The website also have a community for coffee farmers ,researcher's ,enthusiasts for making connection between them. Blog feature for latest articles about research and development. The website have chat-bot, other social media platforms and so many other basic features. This project also have a basic comparison of 5 most popular Keras Models (VGG16, ResNet50, ResNet50V2, IncceptionV3, Xception) for coffee leaf image diseases detection. Accuracy and loss data shows ResNet50V2 Model perfoms better with 81% accuracy among all five Models in only 10 epochs.
